&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Investigate &amp;amp; Resolve:&lt;/strong&gt; Process and thoroughly investigate clinically related patient complaints. Gather additional context from patients, clinic staff, and providers as indicated.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-Functional Triage:&lt;/strong&gt; Coordinate closely with radiology, patient experience, and provider teams during investigations. Triage and escalate concerns to ensure timely, empathetic, and thorough resolution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Clinical Education:&lt;/strong&gt; Follow up directly with patients to provide clarity and education regarding their medical history, scan results, and the scope of a whole-body MRI, resolving concerns with clinical authority and empathy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Case Presentation:&lt;/strong&gt; Prepare and present complex cases for clinical quality review, offering evidence-based recommendations for resolution and systemic prevention.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
