&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At &lt;a href=&quot;http://prenuvo.com/&quot;&gt;Prenuvo&lt;/a&gt;, we are on a mission to flip the paradigm from reactive “sick-care” to proactive health care. Our award-winning whole body scan is fast (under 1 hour), safe (MRI has no ionizing radiation), and non-invasive (no contrast). Our unique integrated stack of optimized hardware, software, and increasingly AI, coupled with the patient-centric experience across our domestic and global clinics, have allowed us to lead the change against “we caught it too late again&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To shift healthcare from reactive to proactive, Prenuvo is building the preventative health clinic network of the future. We currently operate preventative screening clinics across Canada, the United States, the United Kingdom, and Australia. Our patients include both self-referred individuals and physician-referred patients from primary care providers and specialists.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At the heart of our offering is the Prenuvo Scan — a proprietary, non-contrast whole body MRI (WB-MRI) designed to safely and efficiently deliver comprehensive insight into a patient’s physical health in a single visit. Patients receive direct access to their images and radiologist reports through Prenuvo’s suite of patient-facing health applications, empowering them to take control of their health journey.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As we expand our global footprint, we are seeking an innovative and dynamic operational leader to serve as &lt;strong&gt;Clinic Manager&lt;/strong&gt;. This individual will oversee the day-to-day operations of our&lt;strong&gt; Atlanta and Fort Mill clinics&lt;/strong&gt;, as well as &lt;strong&gt;two mobile clinic units&lt;/strong&gt; that rotate throughout the United States. The Clinic Manager will ensure operational excellence, exceptional patient experience, strong financial performance, and high-performing teams across all locations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This role does not provide visa sponsorship. Applicants must be legally authorized to work in the United States at the time of hire and must not require employer sponsorship for a work visa (current or future).&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are passionate about reshaping healthcare through proactive medicine and leading teams in a high-growth, technology-enabled environment, we invite you to join us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead day-to-day operations across our Atlanta and Charlotte clinics and two mobile clinic units operating nationally, ensuring consistent, high-quality execution across all sites.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and maintain a clinic environment and culture that reflects Prenuvo’s mission and the highest standards of modern healthcare delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage, coach, and develop clinic staff and on-site leadership, including Radiology Technologist teams and Patient Liaison teams, fostering accountability, service excellence, and collaboration.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and drive performance across key metrics, including clinic safety, quality of care, patient experience, operational efficiency, utilization, and clinic economics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee staffing models, scheduling, and patient flow to optimize throughput while maintaining an exceptional, hospitality-driven patient experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure regulatory compliance, safety standards, and clinical quality across fixed and mobile locations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate mobile clinic logistics, including site readiness, equipment deployment, vendor management, and operational troubleshooting during national rotations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner cross-functionally with Clinical, Radiology, Clinic Technology, Patient Experience, and other enterprise teams to implement standardized workflows and continuous process improvements.&lt;/li&gt;
